A fire broke out at the main building of Ramathibodi Hospital last night, causing panic and prompting the evacuation of 500 people, including patients.

No patients were injured in the blaze, which occurred in an operating room near the blood bank, X-ray, and delivery room on the second floor of the building at around 7.20pm.

When rescue teams and firefighters arrived at the scene, they found no visible flames, only thick smoke on the floors.

The hospital has suspended operations until further notice.

MedEx is pleased to announce the signing of a Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) with the Center for Medical Genomics (CMG) under the Faculty of Medicine, Ramathibodi Hospital. The signing ceremony took place today at the MedEx office in Bangkok, with MedEx CEO Roshan Adhikari, CMG‚Äôs Head, Prof. Dr. Wasun Chantratita, Ph.D., and team members from both organizations in attendance.

This strategic partnership aims to deliver an expanded range of advanced genetic testing services to MedEx patients while supporting CMG‚Äôs mission in cutting-edge genomics research and development. Together, we are committed to providing innovative, cost-effective genetic diagnostics, featuring new panels based on the latest technologies in nutrigenomics, epigenetics, carrier screening, and more.

This collaboration reflects our shared commitment to advancing personalized healthcare solutions and supporting scientific progress in the field of genomics.
